pr_title: [JENKINS-63022] Make Fingerprint Storage Engine configurable from the config page

timeline.message: Move fingerprint configuration to use descriptors
Move descriptor out of fingerprintstorage class

timeline.bodyText: This part does not seem right. IIRC usage of section does not lead to JSON groouping IIRC. Likely you would get null in this conversion
timeline.author: oleg-nenashev

replies.bodyText: That seems to be working fine
replies.author: stellargo

replies.bodyText: Something's not right here if you have to do this, the configure method should only contain: https://www.jenkins.io/doc/developer/forms/structured-form-submission/#databinding
replies.author: timja

timeline.message: add log for change in fingerprint storage engine
Fingerprints not shown at all if no external fingerprint storage available

timeline.bodyText: Disabled Fingerprint storage impl is a great idea IMHO, but not sure it is a good default here
timeline.author: oleg-nenashev

replies.bodyText: What would you suggest? Local Disk Storage, File Fingerprint Storage seem like other few options.
replies.author: stellargo

replies.bodyText: @oleg-nenashev would be great to hear your vote too :)
replies.author: stellargo

replies.bodyText: I am changing it to Local Fingerprint Storage, mainly due to the face that it goes along with the plugin being called Redis Fingerprint Storage. But I am happy to change it if there are other strong opinions.
replies.author: stellargo
